  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The purpose of the project is to improve adolescent behavioral counseling services in
      healthcare settings with a new Internet/Intranet-based Motivational Enhancement Therapy
      (iMET) intervention that targets the use of tobacco, alcohol, and other drugs.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      We have previously developed and tested in a treatment population a promising MET program for
      alcohol and drug use. We will broaden the MET intervention to also target tobacco use and
      convert the new materials into a self-administered format.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
